Globally acclaimed music star Davido has lauded Kizz Daniel on the massive success of his latest hit song, ‘Buga’. The official video of the biggest Nigerian song in 2022 was released on Wednesday, June 22. The song, which features Cartel Music frontier, Tekno, has been receiving amazing reviews from music lovers globally after the video was launched. Co-produced by Blaise Beatz and Young Willis, ‘Buga’ serves as Vado’s first official music project for the year after the release of his critically acclaimed EP ‘Barnabas’ on November 18, 2012 which recently became the most streamed African album on Audiomack with over 155 million streams.   Osimhen: Right person will leave you if…     Ladipoe reveals reason behind name change from Poe     Actor Alexx Ekubo hails Tacha’s versatility   After announcing the “Buga” video release via his social media pages, the DMW boss took to the post’s comment section on Kizz Daniel’s Instagram page to hail the smash project. “Mega hit,” Davido said. Replying the “Stand Strong” crooner’s positive remark, Vado said: “Bestie” accompanied with a love emoji.